In the EU and America, something else is known as “Feast Day”.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between public holidays and labour-free days.
Workless days are usually church holidays, or are related to significant historical events.
For example, we also celebrate New Year: Both the last day of the old and the first day of the new year are labour-free days - the latter alone so that the New Year’s celebrations can rest.
We have a total of fourteen holidays throughout the year.
The state celebrations are the 15th March, which reminds the Revolution of 1848, and the 23th October, the Memorial Day of the Revolution of 1956.
On August 20, the establishment of the state, on May 1st, the work will be celebrated, on November 1st and 2st, we will commemorate our dead.
In addition, there are two holidays each for Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas.
Since our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall to a weekend, the practice of “workday displacement” has been proven in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
The price of the extended weekends, however, is that we have to work very well on Saturdays before it, or go to school.
When this day, which falls before or after the holiday, is to be finally worked out, has long been established by the Minister of Labour in its own regulation.
The law applies equally to all employers and employers, public employees and public service officials.
Except only companies and facilities in which the operation is continued without interruption, i.e. even on holidays.
Heuer is only confused by the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24, life in this country remains formal, since most of them take time balance for the days between Christmas and New Year’s Day, or the holidays that are removed for it.
The next year, more holidays will fall in the middle of the week, or at the end of the week, so that there will be fewer redispositions on the working days than this year.
The calendar is first placed around the day of work "on the head", so that people can stay at home just four days at the piece.
Saturday, April 26th, will be a working day so that Friday, May 2th, can be a rest day.
The second redeployment is related to the holiday on October 23: on Saturday, October 18, you will have to work on Friday, October 24 in advance.
However, the end of the year will be unrestlessly in the sign of the holidays after everything leaves and remains from December 24, even if New Year’s falls on a Wednesday.
