The Congress agreed to the MIFID Directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
Parallel to the parliamentary development, which today concluded its meeting with the Congress Decision in the Senate on the proposals for additional amendments associated with the project, the Government published the provisions arising out of the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
Representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the Congress and Senate members who had pursued the goal in their negotiations and votes to establish the best possible regime that ensures investor security and regulates each entrepreneur’s activities to guarantee a generally efficient market event.
In addition to modernizing the financial markets, the MIFID, which redefines the securities service regulation, pursues an improvement in investor protection, increased control requirements of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new directive enables both specialized companies and natural or legal entities to provide financial advice and contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory companies that join the investment and mediation companies of securities.
It also expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that regulated circulation markets will add the multilateral systems of the effects of the business and the systems for the internationalization of trade orders, which would eventually compete with current economic operators.
The law requires investment companies to demonstrate the focus of their company profile, the confrontation and ways of dealing with risks on the market, and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate their control task to the CNMV.
The Economic Commission of the Congress later considered further changes, with the decision that the title-owned debt must now be considered complex financial resources due to its high risk level for the investor, which has been confirmed by the U.S. hypothecal and banking crisis.
Furthermore, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the areas of work of diplomated economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the regulation was adopted, which was limited to the areas of work reserved for economists.
On the other hand, the Senate established new positions in the financial sector, as the Economic Mediator who works on a foreign account does not require authorization on the part of the CNMV and can offer its services to commercialize products and simultaneously gain customers multiple investment companies.
