On the early day, United Internet had already participated in the mobile company Drilllich with almost 10 percent.
As part of a capital increase, Drillisch placed 17.4 million new shares worth €106.4 million.
United bought 5.15 million shares of it for 31.4 million euros.
Furthermore, the companies have started talks about marketing cooperations for DSL and mobile products.
"We're strengthening our partnership," a United Internet spokesman explained.
The two companies have established the joint venture MSP to take over the competitor Freenet.
Previously, the two companies want to satisfy themselves with a share of about 10 percent of Freenet and do not make use of their right to take on another 18.49 percent of Freenet, United said on Thursday.
However, the two companies kept all the options open, in particular to further increase the participation in Freenet AG, said.
Talks between the United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership were completed in mid-November.
Freenet’s poker for months and hard to see is part of the consolidation of the German telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million mobile contract customers and 1.27 million DSL and complete connection customers.
The holding of United Internet and Drillisch so far held directly 6.01 percent of Freenet shares.
Now it has been agreed that Drillish will bring about four percent more.
The right to buy 18.49 percent by the investment company Vatas has been agreed in August.
